
Overview of noun cushion

The noun cushion has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (1) shock absorber, shock, cushion -- (a mechanical damper; absorbs energy of sudden impulses; "the old car needed a new set of shocks")
2. cushion -- (the layer of air that supports a hovercraft or similar vehicle)
3. cushion -- (a soft bag filled with air or a mass of padding such as feathers or foam rubber etc.)

